mis_count=[]
mis_per= []
for i in ds.columns:
    missing_count= ds[i].isnull().sum()
    missing_per = (ds[i].isnull().sum()/len(ds))*100
    mis_count.append(missing_count)
    mis_per.append(missing_per)
miss_no = pd.DataFrame({'column': ds.columns,'no.of missing_values':mis_count,'% of missing_values':mis_per})
miss_no

# Trying to fill Lotfrontage col with median in accordance with MSZoning
def lot_f(cols):
    LotFrontage= cols[0]
    MSZoning= cols[1]
    
    if pd.isnull(LotFrontage):
        if MSZoning=='RL':
            return 75
        elif MSZoning=='RM':
            return 50
        elif MSZoning=='FV':
            return 70
        elif MSZoning=='RH':
            return 60
        else:
            return 65
    else:
        return LotFrontage
In [26]:
ds['LotFrontage']= ds[['LotFrontage','MSZoning']].apply(lot_f, axis=1)

def garage(cols):
    gar_yr = cols[0]
    fireplc = cols[1]
    
    if pd.isnull(gar_yr):
        if fireplc==0:
            return 1973
        elif fireplc==1:
            return 1995
        elif fireplc==2:
            return 1970
        else:
            return 1974
    else:
        return gar_yr
    

ds['GarageYrBlt'] = ds[['GarageYrBlt','Fireplaces']].apply(garage,axis=1)

### creating a function to find best algorithm for this model

def find_best_algo(x,y):
    model = {
        'Linear_Regression':{'mod': LinearRegression(),
                            'parameters':{}},
        'knn':{'mod': KNeighborsRegressor(algorithm='auto'),
              'parameters':{'n_neighbors':[2,5,10,20,30,50]}},
        'dec_tree':{'mod': DecisionTreeRegressor(),
                   'parameters': {'criterion':['poisson','friedman_mse','absolute_error','square_error'],
                                 'splitter': ['best','random']}},
        'lasso':{'mod': Lasso(),
                'parameters':{'alpha':[0.1,0.5,1,5,10,20,25,50,75,100,]}},
        'ran_forest':{'mod': RandomForestRegressor(),
                     'parameters':{'n_estimators':[5,10,20,25,50,100],
                                  'criterion': ['poisson','friedman_mse','absolute_error','squared_error']}},
        'xgboost':{'mod':XGBRegressor(),
                  'parameters':{'n_estimators':[5,10,20,50,75,100],
                               'max_depth':[2,3,4,5,7,10],
                               'gamma':[0,0.1,0.25,0.5,0.75,1]}}
    }
    
    scores = []
    for mod_name, mod_params in model.items():
        grid = GridSearchCV(mod_params['mod'], mod_params['parameters'],cv=5, return_train_score=False)
        grid.fit(x,y)
        scores.append({'mod': mod_name,
                      'best_parameters':grid.best_params_,
                      'score': grid.best_score_})
    return pd.DataFrame(scores, columns = ['mod','best_parameters','score'])

find_best_algo(x,y)

    missing_per = (test[i].isnull().sum()/len(test))*100

    mis_per.append(missing_per)

In [45]:
def lot_f(cols):
    LotFrontage= cols[0]
    MSZoning= cols[1]
    
    if pd.isnull(LotFrontage):
        if MSZoning=='RL':
            return 72
        elif MSZoning=='RM':
            return 55
        elif MSZoning=='FV':
            return 70
        elif MSZoning=='RH':
            return 60
        else:
            return 65
    else:
        return LotFrontage
